{"TopicId":177414,"ForumId":16,"TopicTitle":"How do I get a huge asteroid?","CreatedByName":"Laie","CreatedById":110461,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-08-08T18:40:19Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"Laie","CreatedById":110461,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-08-08T18:40:19Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNote, I don\u0027t ask how to find it. I want to know how I can make sure that the Class E I\u0027m heading for will be super-massive. Looking into the savegame, either I\u0027m missing something, or the asteroid mass is just not there until I grab it (well, it says 150t which is patently wrong). Changing the asteroid\u0027\u0027s name will alter the resource density but not the total mass.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOther than trying the RNG until I get lucky, what can I do?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"bewing","CreatedById":154251,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-08-08T19:19:06Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nDo you own the DLC?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Marschig","CreatedById":167206,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-08-08T19:24:52Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223430151\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022177414\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221533753619\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022110461\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Laie\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n40 minutes ago, Laie said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOther than trying the RNG until I get lucky, what c\u003Cspan\u003E\uFEFF\u003C/span\u003Ean I do?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNothing. The mass and shape of the asteroid are determined randomly, when the asteroid becomes visible.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Mahnarch","CreatedById":114432,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-08-19T19:45:13Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-size:16px;\u0022\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022background-color:rgb(255,255,255);color:rgba(0,0,0,.87);text-align:left;\u0022\u003ESchr\u00F6dinger\u0027s Asteroid.\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"XtraChrisP","CreatedById":184353,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-08-20T20:10:57Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223430177\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022177414\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221533755946\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022154251\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022bewing\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn \u200E8\u200E/\u200E8\u200E/\u200E2018 at 3:19 PM, bewing said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nDo you own the DLC?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nInterrogative - what does the DLC do?\u00A0 Does it have some cool\u00A0components that tell you the mass of the asteroid before you launch a mission?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"bewing","CreatedById":154251,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-08-20T22:29:44Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223437207\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022177414\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221534795857\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022184353\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022XtraChrisP\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n2 hours ago, XtraChrisP said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nInterrogative - what does the DLC do?\u00A0 Does it have some cool\u00A0components that tell you the mass of the asteroid before you launch a mission?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe mass and shape of an asteroid are controlled by something called a \u0022seed\u0022. The \u003Cabbr title=\u00221. Original Post(er). The first post in a thread, or the person who posted it. 2. Overpowered. A part or mechanic that upsets game balance by being too powerful.\u0022\u003EOP\u003C/abbr\u003E asked if there were any way besides getting lucky with a random number generator to set the mass. The DLC provides a way of setting the asteroid seed by hand and viewing the changes instantly. Once you know the seed that gets you the results you want, you can copy that seed into the savegame file. And that will conjure up the same asteroid that you were looking at in the DLC.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222018-08-20T22:32:27Z\u0022 title=\u002208/20/2018 10:32  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00225 yr\u0022\u003EAugust 20, 2018\u003C/time\u003E by bewing\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Superfluous J","CreatedById":73725,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-08-20T22:45:23Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223437288\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022177414\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221534804184\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022154251\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022bewing\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n15 minutes ago, bewing said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe mass and shape of an asteroid are controlled by something called a \u0022seed\u0022. The \u003Cabbr title=\u00221. Original Post(er). The first post in a thread, or the person who posted it. 2. Overpowered. A part or mechanic that upsets game balance by being too powerful.\u0022\u003EOP\u003C/abbr\u003E asked if there were any way besides getting lucky with a random number generator to set the mass. The DLC provides a way of setting the asteroid seed by hand and viewing the changes instantly. Once you know the seed that gets you the results you want, you can copy that seed into the savegame file. And that will conjure up the same asteroid that you were looking at in the DLC.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOooh that\u0027s a clever use of the Mission Editor.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Laie","CreatedById":110461,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-08-21T18:49:44Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223437288\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022177414\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221534804184\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022154251\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022bewing\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n20 hours ago, bewing said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nby something called a \u0022seed\u0022\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n...and even if you don\u0027t have the DLC, once you\u0027ve seen a good rock you can note the seed and find it again.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}